Run the builder once first, then train whichever track you want.

If your keys are in `.env.staging`, pass that explicitly because the new configs default to `construction_site/.env`.

```bash
python construction_site/build_construction_site_hf_dataset.py \
  --config construction_site/configs/build_construction_site_hf_dataset_default.json \
  --env-file .env.staging
```

For the strongest first runs, I’d do detect and rule-VQA first:

```bash
python construction_site/train_construction_site_detect.py \
  --config construction_site/configs/cicd/cicd_train_construction_site_detect_offpolicy.json \
  --env-file .env.staging
```

```bash
python construction_site/train_construction_site_query_rule_vqa.py \
  --config construction_site/configs/cicd/cicd_train_construction_site_query_rule_vqa_offpolicy.json \
  --env-file .env.staging
```

For caption query, start with the control config first:

```bash
python construction_site/train_construction_site_query_caption.py \
  --config construction_site/configs/cicd/cicd_train_construction_site_query_caption_control.json \
  --env-file .env.staging
```

After training, benchmark with the `finetune_id` you get back. For example:

```bash
python construction_site/benchmark_construction_site_detect.py \
  --config construction_site/configs/benchmark_construction_site_detect_default.json \
  --env-file .env.staging \
  --finetune-id YOUR_FINETUNE_ID
```

```bash
python construction_site/benchmark_construction_site_query_rule_vqa.py \
  --config construction_site/configs/benchmark_construction_site_query_rule_vqa_default.json \
  --env-file .env.staging \
  --finetune-id YOUR_FINETUNE_ID
```

```bash
python construction_site/benchmark_construction_site_query_caption.py \
  --config construction_site/configs/benchmark_construction_site_query_caption_default.json \
  --env-file .env.staging \
  --finetune-id YOUR_FINETUNE_ID
```

Recommended full sweep order:

1. Build the local derived datasets:

```bash
python construction_site/build_construction_site_hf_dataset.py \
  --config construction_site/configs/build_construction_site_hf_dataset_default.json \
  --env-file .env.staging
```

2. Train detect control first to establish a stable baseline:

```bash
python construction_site/train_construction_site_detect.py \
  --config construction_site/configs/cicd/cicd_train_construction_site_detect_control.json \
  --env-file .env.staging
```

3. Benchmark the detect control run and note the best checkpoint:

```bash
python construction_site/benchmark_construction_site_detect.py \
  --config construction_site/configs/benchmark_construction_site_detect_default.json \
  --env-file .env.staging \
  --finetune-id <DETECT_CONTROL_FINETUNE_ID>
```

4. Train the stronger detect off-policy run:

```bash
python construction_site/train_construction_site_detect.py \
  --config construction_site/configs/cicd/cicd_train_construction_site_detect_offpolicy.json \
  --env-file .env.staging
```

5. Benchmark the detect off-policy run and keep the better of the two detect runs:

```bash
python construction_site/benchmark_construction_site_detect.py \
  --config construction_site/configs/benchmark_construction_site_detect_default.json \
  --env-file .env.staging \
  --finetune-id <DETECT_OFFPOLICY_FINETUNE_ID>
```

6. Train rule-VQA control first:

```bash
python construction_site/train_construction_site_query_rule_vqa.py \
  --config construction_site/configs/cicd/cicd_train_construction_site_query_rule_vqa_control.json \
  --env-file .env.staging
```

7. Benchmark the rule-VQA control run:

```bash
python construction_site/benchmark_construction_site_query_rule_vqa.py \
  --config construction_site/configs/benchmark_construction_site_query_rule_vqa_default.json \
  --env-file .env.staging \
  --finetune-id <RULE_VQA_CONTROL_FINETUNE_ID>
```

8. Train the stronger rule-VQA off-policy run:

```bash
python construction_site/train_construction_site_query_rule_vqa.py \
  --config construction_site/configs/cicd/cicd_train_construction_site_query_rule_vqa_offpolicy.json \
  --env-file .env.staging
```

9. Benchmark the rule-VQA off-policy run and keep the better of the two rule-VQA runs:

```bash
python construction_site/benchmark_construction_site_query_rule_vqa.py \
  --config construction_site/configs/benchmark_construction_site_query_rule_vqa_default.json \
  --env-file .env.staging \
  --finetune-id <RULE_VQA_OFFPOLICY_FINETUNE_ID>
```

10. Train caption control first:

```bash
python construction_site/train_construction_site_query_caption.py \
  --config construction_site/configs/cicd/cicd_train_construction_site_query_caption_control.json \
  --env-file .env.staging
```

11. Benchmark the caption control run:

```bash
python construction_site/benchmark_construction_site_query_caption.py \
  --config construction_site/configs/benchmark_construction_site_query_caption_default.json \
  --env-file .env.staging \
  --finetune-id <CAPTION_CONTROL_FINETUNE_ID>
```

12. If the caption control run is stable, train the caption off-policy variant:

```bash
python construction_site/train_construction_site_query_caption.py \
  --config construction_site/configs/cicd/cicd_train_construction_site_query_caption_offpolicy.json \
  --env-file .env.staging
```

13. Benchmark the caption off-policy run and keep whichever caption run is better:

```bash
python construction_site/benchmark_construction_site_query_caption.py \
  --config construction_site/configs/benchmark_construction_site_query_caption_default.json \
  --env-file .env.staging \
  --finetune-id <CAPTION_OFFPOLICY_FINETUNE_ID>
```

Recommended priority if you want to stop early:

1. detect off-policy
2. rule-VQA off-policy
3. caption control

Keep a short run log as you go:

- detect control finetune id + benchmark json path
- detect off-policy finetune id + benchmark json path
- rule-VQA control finetune id + benchmark json path
- rule-VQA off-policy finetune id + benchmark json path
- caption control finetune id + benchmark json path
- caption off-policy finetune id + benchmark json path
